  Most walls in Rocket League are represented as infinite planes, so car-wall collision uses a Box-Plane algorithm:

  function checkBoxPlaneCollision(boxShape, boxTransform, planeNormal, planeConstant):
      # Get box vertices in world space
      boxVertices = transformBoxCorners(boxShape.halfExtents, boxTransform)

      # Find most negative vertex along plane normal direction
      mostPenetratingDistance = INFINITY
      mostPenetratingPoint = null

      for vertex in boxVertices:
          # Calculate signed distance from vertex to plane
          distance = dot(vertex, planeNormal) - planeConstant

          if distance < mostPenetratingDistance:
              mostPenetratingDistance = distance
              mostPenetratingPoint = vertex

      # If distance is negative, we have collision
      if mostPenetratingDistance < 0:
          # Create contact point
          contactPoint = new ManifoldPoint()
          contactPoint.localPointA = transformToLocalSpace(mostPenetratingPoint, boxTransform)
          contactPoint.localPointB = mostPenetratingPoint - planeNormal * mostPenetratingDistance
          contactPoint.normalWorldOnB = planeNormal
          contactPoint.distance = mostPenetratingDistance

          return contactPoint

      return null

