  4. Impulse Calculation

  The actual impulse is calculated by Bullet's sequential impulse solver. Here's the conceptual algorithm:

  function calculateCollisionImpulse(manifold, bodyA, bodyB, restitution, friction):
      # Get relative velocity at contact point
      relativeVelocity = getRelativeVelocityAtContactPoint(bodyA, bodyB, manifold.localPointA, manifold.localPointB)

      # Calculate normal impulse magnitude
      normalRelativeVelocity = dot(relativeVelocity, manifold.normalWorldOnB)

      # Only apply impulse if objects are moving toward each other
      if normalRelativeVelocity < 0:
          # Calculate normal impulse
          normalImpulseMagnitude = -(1 + restitution) * normalRelativeVelocity
          normalImpulseMagnitude /= calculateContactPointMassRatio(bodyA, bodyB, manifold)

          # Apply position correction for penetration (constraint solving)
          penetrationCorrection = 0.2 * manifold.distance / timeStep  # Baumgarte stabilization
          normalImpulseMagnitude += penetrationCorrection

          # Calculate normal impulse vector
          normalImpulse = manifold.normalWorldOnB * normalImpulseMagnitude

          # Calculate tangential (friction) impulse
          tangentialVelocity = relativeVelocity - manifold.normalWorldOnB * normalRelativeVelocity

          if length(tangentialVelocity) > EPSILON:
              tangentDirection = normalize(tangentialVelocity)
              tangentialImpulseMagnitude = -dot(relativeVelocity, tangentDirection)
              tangentialImpulseMagnitude /= calculateContactPointMassRatio(bodyA, bodyB, manifold)

              # Coulomb friction model
              maxFriction = normalImpulseMagnitude * friction
              tangentialImpulseMagnitude = clamp(tangentialImpulseMagnitude, -maxFriction, maxFriction)

              # Calculate tangential impulse vector
              tangentialImpulse = tangentDirection * tangentialImpulseMagnitude
          else:
              tangentialImpulse = [0, 0, 0]

          # Combined impulse
          impulse = normalImpulse + tangentialImpulse

          # Apply impulse to bodies
          applyImpulse(bodyA, -impulse, manifold.localPointA)
          applyImpulse(bodyB, impulse, manifold.localPointB)

          return impulse

  5. Special Wall-Driving Behavior

  What makes Rocket League unique is its special handling for wall/ceiling driving. After the standard collision impulse is applied, additional
  forces are calculated in the car's update loop:

  function updateCarAutoRoll(car, tickTime):
      # Get up direction based on contact
      if car.internalState.worldContact.hasContact:
          groundUpDir = car.internalState.worldContact.contactNormal

      # Calculate cross products to determine alignment
      crossRightDir = cross(groundUpDir, car.forwardDir)
      crossForwardDir = cross(-groundUpDir, crossRightDir)

      # Calculate torque factors based on misalignment
      rightTorqueFactor = 1 - clamp(dot(car.rightDir, crossRightDir), 0, 1)
      forwardTorqueFactor = 1 - clamp(dot(car.forwardDir, crossForwardDir), 0, 1)

      # Calculate torque directions
      torqueDirRight = car.forwardDir * (dot(car.rightDir, groundUpDir) >= 0 ? -1 : 1)
      torqueDirForward = car.rightDir * (dot(car.forwardDir, groundUpDir) >= 0 ? 1 : -1)

      # Apply autoroll forces
      car.rigidBody.applyCentralForce(-groundUpDir * RLConst::CAR_AUTOROLL_FORCE * UU_TO_BT * CAR_MASS_BT)

      # Apply autoroll torques
      torqueRight = torqueDirRight * rightTorqueFactor * CAR_AUTOROLL_TORQUE
      torqueForward = torqueDirForward * forwardTorqueFactor * CAR_AUTOROLL_TORQUE
      car.rigidBody.applyTorque(car.invInertiaTensorWorld * (torqueForward + torqueRight))

